    "updated_at": "2015-08-10T17:17:02Z",
    "body": "This is a pretty significant piece of functionality to add to process spawning which is also very Unix and/or Linux specific, and I'm pretty wary of it as well because it's all turned off by default. We've tried to make `Command::spawn` as unsurprising as possible, doing as little work as is necessary to actually spawn the child process.\n\nIf we're adding unix-specific extensions, then I'd much rather just start going the route of \"run this closure after the fork\" rather than adding all possible options and combinations to the in-tree implementation.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
