    "created_at": "2015-08-20T00:02:59Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-20T00:02:59Z",
    "body": "Ok the libs team talked about this PR during triage today, and our conclusions were:\n- At this time we feel that an implementation like this does not belong in the standard library quite yet. We already handle all our own file descriptors with CLOEXEC and handling external libraries' file descriptors is a somewhat niche use case. Regardless, though, we all felt that this implementation as-is would require an RFC for inclusion into the standard library.\n- We were in favor of a \"run this closure after fork\" API which would allow implementing this functionality externally on crates.io in the short term. Over time the crates.io implementation could then move into the standard library.\n\nAs a result I'm going to close this PR as we've decided that it'll need an RFC to accept, but feel free to open a PR for the \"run a closure after fork\" API!\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
